WEBVTT

00:42.343 --> 00:46.880
* Baby's black balloon
makes her fly *

00:47.014 --> 00:50.818
* I almost fell into a hole
in your life *
Need to tuck that shirt in.

00:50.951 --> 00:52.520
Yes, sir.

00:52.653 --> 00:56.690
* And you weren't thinking
about tomorrow *

00:56.824 --> 01:00.194
* 'Cause you were the same
as me *

01:00.328 --> 01:05.599
* With all your needs *

01:15.976 --> 01:20.148
* A thousand other boys
could never reach you *

01:21.582 --> 01:24.452
* How could I have been
the one *

01:26.320 --> 01:29.890
* I saw the world
spin beneath you *

01:30.023 --> 01:32.993
* And scatter like ice
from the spoon *

01:33.161 --> 01:38.766
* There was your home *

01:38.899 --> 01:43.671
* Comin' down
the world turned over *

01:43.804 --> 01:48.242
* A dangerous fall
without you there *

01:48.376 --> 01:52.680
* I go on as you get colder *

01:52.813 --> 01:57.251
* Or are you someone
who's there *

02:04.858 --> 02:09.263
* You know the lies
they always told you *

02:09.396 --> 02:12.500
* The only love
you never dreamed *

02:13.834 --> 02:16.804
* Was of things
they never showed you *

02:16.937 --> 02:20.508
* That swallowed the light
from the sun *

02:20.641 --> 02:23.311
* Inside your world *
Oh, somebody's lost.

02:24.745 --> 02:26.747
* Yeah *

02:26.880 --> 02:31.285
* I'm comin' down
to a world turned over *

02:31.419 --> 02:34.988
* A dangerous fall
without you there *

02:35.122 --> 02:40.294
* As I go on
I will lead you homeward *

02:40.428 --> 02:44.998
* All because all *

02:45.132 --> 02:47.235
* I'll become *

02:47.335 --> 02:51.705
* You became to me **

02:56.510 --> 02:59.046
Sweet ride.
Who scored this?

02:59.247 --> 03:02.483
Probably some spoiled-ass
mother--
Shiverson!

03:06.254 --> 03:10.591
[ Boy ] Look at that chrome
on that thing, man.
[ Boy #2 ] Very nice.

03:10.724 --> 03:13.294
It's, uh, a very nice gift.

03:13.427 --> 03:15.095
I'm sure you're disappointed.

03:15.263 --> 03:18.766
Why, 'cause my father
can't come to graduation?

03:18.899 --> 03:22.770
He's in London, in the middle
of a deal that's gonna double
our stock price.

03:22.903 --> 03:27.275
I don't need him to jeopardize
that for some bullshit
graduation ceremony.

03:27.408 --> 03:29.277
Sorry, sir.

03:29.377 --> 03:31.279
The graduation ceremony
is not bull.

03:31.379 --> 03:33.347
Certainly not
when you're valedictorian.

03:33.481 --> 03:36.083
With all due respect, sir,
I didn't spend four years
here...

03:36.284 --> 03:39.853
just so I could give
a "go get 'em" speech
to a bunch of whining children.

03:39.987 --> 03:44.091
Well, you know the rule
about cars on campus.

03:44.292 --> 03:48.161
So I'll keep it
in the motor pool until
after Sunday's ceremony,

03:48.296 --> 03:50.298
and then it's all yours.

03:50.398 --> 03:53.901
So, uh, if that's it--

03:57.971 --> 04:01.141
My sister's boyfriend's
got one. It's lickety, bro.

04:01.309 --> 04:03.143
It's like a G-4
in a tail wind.

04:03.311 --> 04:05.078
I can have sex
with a car like that.

04:05.212 --> 04:07.315
Just don't burn your
wood drill on the tailpipe.

04:07.381 --> 04:10.217
No, I mean I could have sex
with a woman if I had a car
like that.

04:10.351 --> 04:13.487
Steve, you couldn't have sex
with a woman if you gave her
a car like that.

04:13.621 --> 04:17.124
So he wouldn't even let you take
it out for a quick spin?
A little shakedown cruise?

04:17.325 --> 04:21.562
I don't need
Shiverson's permission
to take my own car out.

04:22.596 --> 04:25.032
Valet key.
It was on his desk.

04:42.950 --> 04:45.753
* I've never been here before *

04:45.886 --> 04:51.525
* Didn't know where to go
Never met you before *

04:52.726 --> 04:55.363
[ Tires Squealing ]

04:55.496 --> 04:59.433
** [ Continues ]
[ Whooping ]

05:09.142 --> 05:14.114
* You can do all the things
that you learn to do *

05:14.247 --> 05:19.019
* All around on the ground
Pick a part that's new *

05:19.152 --> 05:23.691
* You can do all the things
that you like to do *

05:23.824 --> 05:26.527
* All around, upside down **

05:26.660 --> 05:28.962
[ Everyone Chattering ]

05:29.096 --> 05:33.100
I swear I'm bein' blackmailed
into this.
Ha. Not true.

05:33.233 --> 05:35.503
Somebody else better be up there
takin' the knife after me.

05:35.636 --> 05:37.571
Just do it already.

05:40.408 --> 05:44.478
[ Tapping On Table ]
Can I ask you
a really big favor?

05:44.612 --> 05:48.716
I have a date tonight.
It's my graduation night.

05:48.849 --> 05:50.451
I know. I'm sorry.
I forgot that I was closing.

05:50.584 --> 05:52.653
I would ask Mom, but she's
baby-sitting Patty.

05:52.786 --> 05:57.858
Please, Sam? Finish my shift
for me. I promise you
I will owe you so big-time.

05:57.991 --> 05:59.760
You already owe me
your firstborn.

05:59.893 --> 06:02.630
Oh, well, you can have her.
She likes you better anyway.

06:06.667 --> 06:09.937
- Your turn, sucker.
- So, do I carve it up?

06:12.573 --> 06:16.544
I have to do my sister
a giant favor that
she'd never do for me.

06:16.677 --> 06:20.514
Oh, come on.
I do you favors.

06:20.648 --> 06:23.884
She hasn't had a date
in like a year.

06:24.017 --> 06:25.018
All right.

06:33.994 --> 06:36.597
[ Steve ] Look,
what are we doin', Kelley?

06:36.730 --> 06:39.833
You guys hungry?
What, do you have
a death wish?

06:39.967 --> 06:42.369
The Putties hate our guts.
Can we just leave?

06:42.503 --> 06:45.639
[ Chuckles ]
Let's eat.

07:17.104 --> 07:19.973
What the hell's
he doing in?

07:21.809 --> 07:23.511
So, what'll it be?

07:25.679 --> 07:29.517
Uh, what's good here?
Besides the help.

07:30.784 --> 07:33.153
[ Chuckles ]
Can I take your order?

07:33.286 --> 07:34.588
Yeah.

07:36.256 --> 07:38.291
Do you really make
your own ice cream?

07:38.425 --> 07:40.393
With our very own hands.

07:40.528 --> 07:43.764
How does one actually
make ice cream?

07:43.897 --> 07:45.799
[ Whispers ]
It's a secret family recipe.

07:45.933 --> 07:49.169
- You won't even tell me?
- Not even you.

07:49.302 --> 07:53.106
- I bet I can get it
out of you.
- Better men have tried.

07:55.709 --> 07:58.846
[ Chuckles ]
They don't look like
better men to me.

07:58.979 --> 08:02.716
Three vanilla shakes
will be fine. Let me
get that for you, Kelley.

08:04.885 --> 08:07.955
If you check out my ass
when I walk away,

08:08.088 --> 08:10.658
your shake will be
in your lap.

08:17.731 --> 08:20.668
[ Whispers ]
Let's just get out of here.

08:24.805 --> 08:26.640
Are you trying to get
at me, Richie?

08:26.774 --> 08:32.846
- "Richie"?
- Yeah. Richie Rich.
That's your name, isn't it?

08:32.980 --> 08:35.582
Let's just get outta here.
No, he's right.

08:35.649 --> 08:38.751
You can tell a lot
from appearances.

08:38.885 --> 08:43.056
Look at him.
I would say that you're poor.

08:43.190 --> 08:45.759
They're not homeless
or anything,

08:45.893 --> 08:47.628
just run of the mill poor.

08:48.829 --> 08:51.999
Judging from that lazy grin,

08:52.132 --> 08:54.201
I'd say you're not
too bright either.

08:54.334 --> 08:55.903
Kell, let's just go.

08:56.036 --> 09:00.841
- Take it easy!
- Violence. The first
refuge of the poor and--

09:02.109 --> 09:04.411
[ Samantha ]
Hey, cut it out!

09:04.612 --> 09:07.615
Hey, you want to get
yourself hurt, or what?
Who's gonna hurt me? Him?

09:07.715 --> 09:09.950
Huh?

09:10.083 --> 09:13.120
Get out!
Kell, let's
just go, man.

09:16.256 --> 09:19.660
- Later, Richie.
- You can count on it.

09:22.630 --> 09:25.733
You're lucky
I don't kick you out.
He was all over you, and I--

09:25.866 --> 09:28.736
You were just picking a fight
while I'm in charge.

09:28.869 --> 09:31.271
[ Softly ]
I can't even talk to you.

09:33.273 --> 09:35.142
Sam.

09:36.744 --> 09:38.912
Let's just go, Kelley.
What are we doin' here, man?

09:43.817 --> 09:46.654
- Hey, I wanna know
one thing before I go.
- What's that?

09:46.787 --> 09:50.691
What freaks you out more?
Gettin' bailed out
by your girlfriend...

09:50.824 --> 09:54.094
or knowing that she was
adding me to her fantasy file?

09:57.564 --> 09:59.767
[ Tires Squeal ]

10:05.605 --> 10:07.675
What did he say?

10:07.808 --> 10:10.043
I think he just said,
"Come kick my ass."

10:10.177 --> 10:13.046
[ Laughing ]
Hell, that was
awesome, man.

10:13.180 --> 10:17.417
You should've seen their faces.
Should've seen your face, man!
You were scared shitless.

10:17.550 --> 10:20.520
Yeah, right, dude.
You make me feel better about--

10:20.654 --> 10:22.923
Oh, my God.
Holy shit.

10:35.635 --> 10:37.905
Hey, Richie.
Come and get it.

10:38.038 --> 10:39.773
Come on, farm boy.

10:41.174 --> 10:44.712
- Yeah!
- Push it down.
Get 'em!

10:46.947 --> 10:50.818
I should remind you not to
go over 50 miles per hour
for the first thousand miles.

10:50.951 --> 10:53.220
Shut up, Charlie.

10:55.422 --> 10:59.059
Are there any air bags
back here?
Shut up, Charlie!

11:01.428 --> 11:03.063
Hi, pussies.

11:18.846 --> 11:21.014
This isn't fun.
I'm not having fun.

11:29.089 --> 11:30.991
[ Steve ]
What are you doing?

11:32.392 --> 11:34.762
[ Shouts ]

11:36.096 --> 11:39.099
That's what I'm
talkin' about!

11:41.334 --> 11:43.871
- Punch it!
- [ Steve ]
He's right behind you.

11:52.412 --> 11:55.015
- [ Pedestrians Screaming ]
- [ Tires Screeching ]

12:51.204 --> 12:53.240
Samantha.

13:02.115 --> 13:04.351
[ Sirens Wailing ]

13:08.088 --> 13:13.193
We're gonna have a few
questions at the station,
so get in the back of the car.

13:14.061 --> 13:16.329
Watch your heads.

13:25.238 --> 13:27.941
You should probably
come down to the hospital
and get checked out.

13:28.075 --> 13:30.343
Really, I'm fine.

13:33.881 --> 13:36.316
You know who I am, son?

13:36.449 --> 13:38.351
Sheriff Cavanaugh?

13:38.485 --> 13:40.787
My wife is Jo Cavanaugh,

13:40.921 --> 13:43.556
and her mother was Mable.

13:45.525 --> 13:48.896
You almost took my daughter
from me tonight.

13:48.996 --> 13:50.497
Roll your eyes at me
one more time,

13:50.630 --> 13:52.365
this shit heap you're in
is just gonna get deeper.

13:52.499 --> 13:55.903
Sheriff, if this is a threat--
[ Grunts ]

13:55.969 --> 14:00.707
What the hell is goin' on?
The nice thing about my job is I
don't have to threaten anybody.

14:00.908 --> 14:03.010
Grab them too.

14:03.143 --> 14:05.979
Me? Hey, I was
practically kidnapped!

14:12.319 --> 14:14.187
I understand you're
from New York, Your Honor.

14:14.321 --> 14:17.524
- Born and bred.
- Me too. Upper East Side.

14:17.657 --> 14:22.062
Good for you. But we're
not bonding here, so don't
get your dress over your head.

14:27.234 --> 14:30.938
Mr. Morse, I presume.
Good.

14:34.674 --> 14:38.946
Your Honor, we were thinking
that some sort of probation
would be appropriate.

14:39.012 --> 14:41.481
[ Judge ]
Probation, huh?
Let's think it through.

14:41.614 --> 14:45.818
They talk to a probation
officer once a week
for a year or so.

14:45.953 --> 14:49.957
Maybe do a couple hundred hours
of volunteer work
at a community center.

14:50.023 --> 14:51.959
That what you had in mind?

14:52.025 --> 14:55.528
Something like that, yes.
Not gonna happen,
but thanks for playin'.

14:55.662 --> 15:00.633
Gentlemen, I don't know
what your lawyers told you,

15:00.767 --> 15:02.970
but this
is pretty serious stuff.

15:03.070 --> 15:07.207
A probation walk was fine
for the other boys, the ones
in the cars with you,

15:07.340 --> 15:10.710
but you two were the cowboys
behind the wheel.

15:10.843 --> 15:14.381
We're gonna have to do
something different with you.

15:14.514 --> 15:18.385
I understand Mr. Arnold has been
contracted to rebuild Mable's.

15:18.518 --> 15:20.587
Yes, that's right,
Your Honor.

15:20.720 --> 15:22.990
We'd like to make
another suggestion,
with the court's permission.

15:23.056 --> 15:27.460
- Shoot.
- Mr. Morse has graciously
offered to pay...

15:27.594 --> 15:32.199
for the restaurant,
as long as all charges
against his son are dropped.

15:32.332 --> 15:35.002
- That sounds nice, huh?
- We thought it appropriate.

15:35.135 --> 15:38.171
Not in my court.
In my court, you fix
what you broke.

15:38.305 --> 15:43.476
So here it is.
I'd be willing to dismiss
all charges in this case...

15:43.610 --> 15:46.313
if the boys volunteer
for community service...

15:46.446 --> 15:49.282
working with the crew
rebuilding Mable's Table.

15:49.416 --> 15:53.553
It's a chance to put back
what you took,

15:53.686 --> 15:55.322
and maybe, just maybe,

15:55.455 --> 15:58.291
it'll not only result
in the building of
a restaurant,

15:58.425 --> 16:01.461
but in the building
of character as well.

16:03.030 --> 16:06.566
You can have some time
to talk it over
with your attorneys.

16:06.699 --> 16:09.636
That's okay, Judge.
We'll take the deal.

16:09.769 --> 16:13.640
Your Honor, that's completely
impractical for Calvin.
Where would he live?

16:13.773 --> 16:18.378
Even if Rallston would take him,
the dorms are closed
for the summer.

16:18.511 --> 16:21.148
The nearest motel is 30 miles
away, Your Honor,

16:21.281 --> 16:23.550
and his driver's license
has been revoked.

16:23.683 --> 16:27.520
Actually, we have a room
above our garage.

16:27.654 --> 16:31.324
The boy could pay rent.

16:31.458 --> 16:34.694
It works for me.
How about you, Counselor?

16:36.463 --> 16:38.598
That's acceptable to us
as well, Your Honor.

16:44.804 --> 16:48.075
Another Rallston boy
takes a bite out of
the Cavanaugh family.

16:48.208 --> 16:51.478
I had nothing to do with this
one. I wasn't even here.
Exactly.

16:51.611 --> 16:54.147
You--
Nobody's blaming anybody.

16:54.281 --> 16:56.816
It would have been nice
if one of you'd called me
when the trouble first started.

16:56.949 --> 17:00.720
I remember when Jesse
and Alice carved this.

17:04.590 --> 17:08.528
Mom, remember what you said
to me so many times?

17:08.661 --> 17:11.397
As long as we're all alive,
it's nothing more
than a bad day. Right?

17:11.531 --> 17:14.101
Yeah. We can beat
a bad day. Right?

17:14.233 --> 17:17.470
[ Sighs ]
Right.

17:23.276 --> 17:26.546
They're here!
They're here!

17:37.490 --> 17:40.793
That's because he doesn't
like the percentage
we're offering.

17:40.927 --> 17:43.263
Then he's gonna have to
come up with a better deal.

17:43.396 --> 17:45.132
It's a matter--
Yeah. I gotta go.

17:47.334 --> 17:49.802
Listen, I worked everything out
with these people,
including your meals.

17:49.936 --> 17:54.040
So all you're gonna need
is some spending money.

17:54.174 --> 17:55.575
This should last you
for a while,

17:55.708 --> 18:00.147
but if you need some more,
you just call my office.

18:00.280 --> 18:05.152
I'm gonna be a little hard
to reach for the next few weeks.
Okay.

18:05.218 --> 18:06.853
Hello there.
Good afternoon.

18:06.986 --> 18:12.359
Hey.
I'm running a little late,
and I have a flight to catch,

18:12.492 --> 18:15.027
so I assume there's nothing
else we need to discuss.

18:15.162 --> 18:20.633
No. I think we're good.
Your room's right above
the garage if you want to go up.

18:25.438 --> 18:27.174
Now, you remember
what I told you.

18:27.274 --> 18:30.009
Keep your eyes forward
on the important things.

18:30.177 --> 18:32.412
Yes, sir.

19:03.243 --> 19:05.077
That's Ralph.

19:05.212 --> 19:07.480
He lives here too.

19:09.349 --> 19:11.584
Perfect.

19:16.589 --> 19:18.758
Maybe I should
take him up a plate.

19:18.891 --> 19:22.495
Honey, we offered.
When he gets hungry,
he'll come down.

19:22.629 --> 19:26.666
Let him starve.
After everything he did.

19:29.236 --> 19:31.571
How many cars were
in that race, anyway?

19:34.341 --> 19:37.844
- Two.
- Was he driving both of them?

19:41.314 --> 19:43.883
I think he's hot.

19:46.085 --> 19:48.321
[ Choking ]

20:23.823 --> 20:26.793
My dad's already got me
fixing fence posts
till I'm 90.

20:26.926 --> 20:31.498
Plus the work at Mable's.
I got enough problems
without you being mad at me.

20:31.631 --> 20:34.867
I just think you could
have been the bigger man.
That's all.

20:36.403 --> 20:39.406
All right. Okay.

20:42.275 --> 20:46.979
Well. Is everything
still okay with us?

20:50.016 --> 20:51.918
[ Whistles ]

20:52.051 --> 20:54.721
God, we haven't done that
in about a hundred years.

21:01.494 --> 21:05.064
[ Sputtering ]
[ Laughing ]

21:05.197 --> 21:06.833
You were never
very good at that.

21:06.966 --> 21:08.835
Ah, but I'm the one
that taught you.

21:08.968 --> 21:11.904
I'm the one
that mastered it.
[ Sputtering ]

21:12.038 --> 21:13.940
[ Both Laughing ]

21:14.073 --> 21:16.343
[ Whistles ]

21:22.349 --> 21:24.351
[ Pounding ]

21:24.451 --> 21:28.187
Time to get up, Richie.
Gotta evacuate the cows.

21:28.355 --> 21:31.558
Is there a gas leak
or something?

21:33.960 --> 21:37.096
Evacuating.

21:37.229 --> 21:40.767
You're out of your mind
if you think I'm touchin'
that thing.

21:47.206 --> 21:49.275
Well, good morning.

21:49.409 --> 21:54.614
- Can I fix you something?
- Breakfast is served
after morning chores.

21:54.747 --> 21:59.386
I don't eat breakfast.
I was just coming in to find out
when we leave for work.

22:00.420 --> 22:02.655
Be at the truck
in 20 minutes.

22:20.773 --> 22:24.210
Not getting tired,
are you, Richie?
No.

22:24.411 --> 22:28.781
Got an extra hour's sleep
while you were fondling
your cows.

22:28.915 --> 22:31.418
[ Mr. Arnold ]
That's lunch!

22:31.551 --> 22:35.121
Break time, guys.
Food and drink's in the cooler.

22:35.254 --> 22:38.090
I'll get my own lunch.

22:38.224 --> 22:41.594
Suit yourself.
Lunch! Let's go.

22:42.495 --> 22:44.797
Okay, I'm outta here.

22:44.931 --> 22:47.033
[ Kiss ]
Good to be your father.

22:47.166 --> 22:49.436
Good to be
your daughter.

22:51.137 --> 22:53.039
Do you know what I was
thinking about last night, Mom?
What?

22:53.172 --> 22:56.443
They're giving us all this money
to rebuild. Right?

22:56.509 --> 23:00.780
So we can start all over
from scratch and have fun.
We can go to antique stores...

23:00.913 --> 23:03.082
and flea markets
and get funky furniture.

23:03.215 --> 23:06.185
We could do that.
We could stop on the way
back from Dr. Falco's.

23:06.318 --> 23:09.288
[ Sighs ]
I completely forgot
about Dr. Falco.

23:09.456 --> 23:13.626
That's a good sign.
I guess your knee
hasn't been bothering you.

23:13.760 --> 23:15.562
Mom, my knee's fine.

23:15.695 --> 23:19.632
So can I cancel Dr. Falco?
No.

23:20.900 --> 23:23.670
Oh, I hate this.
I know.

23:23.803 --> 23:26.873
He's just making sure
everything's still okay.

23:27.006 --> 23:29.676
My knee's fine. Why do we
have to keep coming here?

23:29.809 --> 23:33.079
Because the doctor said so.
Samantha?

23:41.120 --> 23:44.156
When something is taken away
from us so violently,

23:44.290 --> 23:46.493
like the recent fire
at Mable's Table,

23:46.626 --> 23:49.729
we are forced to ask questions.

23:49.862 --> 23:53.199
Was it simply
a terrible accident?

23:53.332 --> 23:55.735
Atoms colliding at random?

23:55.868 --> 23:59.506
A result of young people
making poor choices?

23:59.639 --> 24:02.074
Or was it the hand of God?

24:02.208 --> 24:07.179
A part of a larger plan
that He might have for us?

24:10.049 --> 24:11.918
Hey, Jasper. Where's
your new pal Kelley today?

24:12.051 --> 24:14.253
Oh, he's at your house,
getting busy with your mom.

24:14.386 --> 24:17.790
Really? 'Cause last night
when I was with your mom,
she said he was kind of cute.

24:17.924 --> 24:20.727
It made me jealous.
Enough with the
mother thing already.

24:20.860 --> 24:22.762
I second that.
Excuse me.

24:22.895 --> 24:25.765
What? I'm just saying
enough's enough.
I like your mom.

24:25.898 --> 24:29.669
Hey, guys. We're goin'
skinny dipping tonight.
Wanna come?

24:29.802 --> 24:33.439
- Dad's making me work.
- My man looks good naked.

24:33.573 --> 24:35.908
[ Giggles ]
Yeah, I'm like Tarzan.

24:38.244 --> 24:40.112
See you later?
Mm-hmm.

25:25.357 --> 25:27.827
[ Crowd Applauding Nearby ]

25:42.875 --> 25:46.012
Good afternoon,
classmates and invited guests.

25:46.145 --> 25:50.216
Today we mark the end
of our infancy,

25:50.349 --> 25:52.384
the end of our childhood,

25:52.518 --> 25:54.621
the end of our beginning.

25:54.721 --> 25:58.057
with hope to the future,

25:58.190 --> 26:02.629
and then the future
becomes the past.

26:02.762 --> 26:06.866
At what point in our lives
do we begin thinking about
the past and the future?

26:06.999 --> 26:10.970
I know when I was a child
I never gave them much thought.

26:11.838 --> 26:13.439
I miss those days.

26:15.407 --> 26:20.446
Robert Frost once wrote about
his carefree youth, climbing
the branches of birch trees.

26:20.647 --> 26:25.918
He wrote, "So I was once myself
a swinger of birches,

26:27.553 --> 26:30.723
and so I dream of going back
to be."

26:33.525 --> 26:35.394
So do I, Mr. Frost.

26:35.527 --> 26:37.664
So do I.

26:37.764 --> 26:40.967
[ Applause ]

26:53.913 --> 26:57.049
Let's go. You ready?

26:57.784 --> 27:00.687
I'm not hungry.

27:06.358 --> 27:09.862
We'll be right up.

27:13.332 --> 27:16.168
These folks are being
very gracious, don't you think?

27:16.302 --> 27:19.939
Inviting you to their home after
everything that's happened.

27:20.072 --> 27:23.209
Look. I come to work.
I do my job. Okay?

27:23.342 --> 27:27.279
That's the deal I made.
My probation doesn't say
anything...

27:27.413 --> 27:30.750
about me sittin' around
spittin' out watermelon seeds
with you people.

27:30.883 --> 27:35.722
I gotta tell you, son.
I don't think you're gonna make
the summer with this attitude.

27:35.788 --> 27:38.090
I'm not your son.

27:38.224 --> 27:40.259
No, you're not.

28:07.920 --> 28:10.222
Grandpa!
Hey.

28:10.356 --> 28:14.761
Whoa. How's my girl?
Earl, missin'
a great lunch here.

28:14.861 --> 28:17.163
I'll catch up.
We have tons of food,
baby.

28:20.532 --> 28:23.235
Jo, appreciate this.
Thank you.

28:23.369 --> 28:26.138
You guys have been working
so hard, you deserve it.

28:26.272 --> 28:28.307
Where's Sam?

28:43.089 --> 28:46.859
Don't worry, I won't tell
anybody you actually ate.

28:50.696 --> 28:55.034
I'd like it
if you'd stop sulking
long enough to try.

28:55.167 --> 28:59.105
I'm not sulking.
Oh, come on.

28:59.238 --> 29:01.507
We invite you over
for lunch.

29:01.640 --> 29:05.044
And you decide
to sit out here like
a really big baby.

29:07.513 --> 29:12.484
And at what point did I give you
the impression that it was okay
to come out here and insult me?

29:53.993 --> 29:56.028
Stay away from Samantha.

29:56.162 --> 29:59.231
Relax. I'm not makin'
a move on your girlfriend.

29:59.365 --> 30:03.369
You think I'm worried
about that?
Don't know, don't care.

30:04.603 --> 30:06.538
Stay away from her.

30:06.672 --> 30:09.041
Or what, exactly?

30:09.175 --> 30:12.144
Listen, Richie.
You don't want to mess
with me. All right?

30:12.278 --> 30:14.646
Ooh. Scary.

30:14.780 --> 30:19.518
I'm surprised you even bother
with a girlfriend, you got such
a good thing with those cows.

30:19.651 --> 30:21.553
What's that supposed
to mean?
Aw, come on.

30:21.687 --> 30:23.923
You got yourself
a regular harem out there.

30:24.056 --> 30:29.028
Get your hands up
their skirt every morning.
You serenade them every night.

30:29.161 --> 30:32.398
That, or you're
in love with a 600-pounder
who likes to chew her vomit.

30:32.531 --> 30:36.735
You know what I'm really
doin' up there, Richie?
What's that?

30:36.869 --> 30:38.837
Your mother.

30:49.015 --> 30:51.317
What's your problem,
man?

30:58.724 --> 31:01.027
Hey! Hey!

31:01.160 --> 31:03.495
Stop it!
What's the matter
with you?

31:03.629 --> 31:06.999
Come on. Get up.
Let's go. Let's go.

31:07.934 --> 31:09.969
Hey, hey!
You can quit right now.

31:10.102 --> 31:12.338
Right now.

31:13.605 --> 31:14.941
I quit.

31:16.775 --> 31:20.179
You can't quit.
It isn't a job.
It's a sentence! God.

31:20.312 --> 31:22.982
I'll talk with that kid.
No, no! Earl.

31:23.115 --> 31:25.952
Just wait. Let him go.
Let him cool off, okay?

31:26.085 --> 31:28.587
You. Look at me.
You know better.

31:28.720 --> 31:30.957
Go to the truck.
Now.

31:36.362 --> 31:40.499
** [ Playing Awkwardly ]

31:48.975 --> 31:51.377
[ Sighs ]
[ Exhales ]

31:51.510 --> 31:56.415
Albert. I expect you
to know that piece
by next Tuesday. Okay.

31:56.548 --> 32:01.087
Okay.
Okay.
Get outta here.

32:07.559 --> 32:10.329
Come and sit.

32:11.430 --> 32:16.068
Dad already gave me
an earful, so, uh--

32:19.071 --> 32:21.140
You still remember
how to play?

32:21.273 --> 32:26.078
** [ Jazz Phrase ]

32:27.613 --> 32:31.450
Music's always been our thing,
hasn't it?

32:31.583 --> 32:33.619
You and me?

32:37.056 --> 32:38.690
It'll always be
something we share.

32:44.696 --> 32:47.799
I imagine you think
Kelley's real lucky.

32:47.933 --> 32:50.069
Gets to have all that money.

32:50.202 --> 32:52.738
Seems to have
the whole world
in his hands.

32:54.506 --> 32:57.376
Ever consider maybe
you're the lucky one?

33:01.613 --> 33:04.716
I didn't see a mother
in that courtroom.

33:22.501 --> 33:26.472
[ Thud ]
You killed him.

33:26.605 --> 33:28.407
Killed who?
What are you talkin' about?

33:28.540 --> 33:30.376
You just threw him
in the garbage!

33:30.509 --> 33:34.413
What did he ever do to you?
Are we talkin'
about the mouse?

33:34.546 --> 33:37.416
You're just a jerk.
I'm never speaking
to you again.

33:49.095 --> 33:53.132
I'm just so sick of not being
able to buy good clothes
around here.

33:53.265 --> 33:55.567
So, you want to come
to Boston next week?

34:05.611 --> 34:06.745
I'm hot.

34:08.380 --> 34:10.649
I need to go
get something to drink.

34:27.733 --> 34:29.400
My sister hates you.

34:29.534 --> 34:32.138
Why? She doesn't
even know me.

34:33.038 --> 34:35.206
Well, she hates you
on principle.

34:35.341 --> 34:38.409
I'm glad it's not personal.

34:43.382 --> 34:46.217
What was that about?

34:46.351 --> 34:49.288
I killed Ralph.

34:50.456 --> 34:53.192
Oh. You could
get arrested for that.

34:53.324 --> 34:56.161
Will there be handcuffs?

34:58.497 --> 35:00.832
Do you want handcuffs?

35:02.401 --> 35:04.603
Depends on who's
puttin' them on.

35:04.736 --> 35:07.673
Probably the sheriff,
so don't get too excited.

35:10.842 --> 35:13.812
Do you always bring
the sheriff on dates?

35:16.315 --> 35:19.218
Not if I'm the one
who's breaking the law.

35:26.024 --> 35:28.260
Meet me tonight.

35:46.245 --> 35:49.114
Let's see what you got,
slugger.

35:49.248 --> 35:51.350
Okay.

36:07.533 --> 36:10.302
Oh, there's a shot!

36:10.436 --> 36:13.672
It's a home run!
That wasn't my best pitch.

36:13.805 --> 36:18.244
- Baseball's not really
my sport.
- What is?

36:18.377 --> 36:19.978
Track.
Really?

36:20.111 --> 36:22.748
Running hurdles.
I was pretty good,
but then...

36:22.881 --> 36:26.051
cracking your kneecap
will change that one
in a hurry.

36:26.252 --> 36:28.720
Ouch.
Yeah.

36:28.854 --> 36:31.757
I had a full ride
to B.U.

36:31.890 --> 36:34.693
So I'll just
have to pay for college
the old-fashioned way now.

36:34.826 --> 36:37.296
Student loans.

36:38.397 --> 36:41.267
What's after college?

36:41.333 --> 36:43.569
Probably med school.

36:45.471 --> 36:48.374
Although I'd like to toy
with the idea...

36:48.507 --> 36:51.610
of spending my whole life
here in the woods,
writing poetry.

36:51.743 --> 36:56.382
Yeah. Med school
sounds a bit more practical.

36:59.918 --> 37:03.722
There are worse things to be
than a swinger of birches.

37:04.923 --> 37:06.958
You know that poem?

37:08.294 --> 37:09.795
My favorite.

37:12.931 --> 37:15.334
I heard your speech.

37:16.302 --> 37:18.470
What?

37:22.674 --> 37:26.678
I saw you walking.
And you followed me?

37:28.647 --> 37:32.751
I liked it.
Honest.

37:35.821 --> 37:37.989
It's a sad poem too,
though, isn't it?

37:39.591 --> 37:44.763
Life is too much like
a pathless wood where
your face burns and tickles.

37:47.198 --> 37:50.502
The cobwebs,
broken across it.

37:50.636 --> 37:54.973
And one eye is weeping
from having a twig
lash across.

37:55.106 --> 37:59.345
I'd like to get away
from Earth a while,

37:59.411 --> 38:02.881
and then come back to it
and begin over.

38:18.464 --> 38:21.533
What are you thinking?

38:21.667 --> 38:25.937
I was just thinking about that
ham sandwich you brought me
the other day.

38:28.474 --> 38:30.676
What about it?

38:30.809 --> 38:34.613
I was just wondering
if there was mustard, or--

38:58.770 --> 39:02.040
That was nice.
Nice?

39:02.173 --> 39:06.077
There was a lot going on
in "nice."
Like what?

39:28.199 --> 39:33.439
[ Patty ]
What name should I give him?
His name should be Mikey.

39:33.505 --> 39:39.177
How about Mikey Red?
Mikey Red is
a very good name.

39:39.310 --> 39:42.313
Mom. What about this one?

39:42.448 --> 39:44.349
Ah, it's okay.
It doesn't thrill me.

39:44.483 --> 39:47.218
Mom. Mommy,
I have to go tinkle.

39:47.352 --> 39:50.055
I'll take her.
It's all right.

39:50.188 --> 39:52.491
Thanks, Mom.
Okay.

39:57.362 --> 40:00.165
What, already?
You keep staring at me.
Mm-hmm.

40:02.000 --> 40:04.470
You're seeing him,
aren't you?

40:06.638 --> 40:09.541
Who?
Don't even think
about denying it.

40:09.675 --> 40:12.511
I know that look, Sam.
I have had that look.

40:13.812 --> 40:16.114
We just hung out.
No big deal.

40:16.247 --> 40:19.350
Are you crazy?
You know what those
Rallston guys are like.

40:19.485 --> 40:21.587
No. I know what
your Rallston guy was like.
Excuse me.

40:21.720 --> 40:24.690
Trust me.
They are all the same.

40:24.823 --> 40:26.558
You don't think I know
what you're feeling?

40:26.692 --> 40:31.129
Hmm? He seems exciting
to you, different, maybe
even a little dangerous.

40:31.262 --> 40:34.099
Believe me, honey.
I have been there.

40:36.001 --> 40:40.472
I'm not marrying him,
Jen. We're just--
Hanging out.

40:42.474 --> 40:45.076
Right.

40:45.210 --> 40:47.212
Right.

40:55.453 --> 41:00.025
[ Crowd Cheering ]

41:00.158 --> 41:02.193
[ Shop Bell Jingles ]

41:04.530 --> 41:07.699
[ TV Continues, Indistinct ]

41:18.544 --> 41:21.212
Hey. I thought
we were gonna meet later.

41:21.346 --> 41:24.616
Well, when I saw you
walk in, I couldn't wait.

41:24.750 --> 41:28.019
I told Malcolm
I was walking home.

41:28.153 --> 41:31.957
Your, uh, good buddy
Pete's up there.
Yeah, I know.

41:32.090 --> 41:35.093
So I can't buy
a soda?

41:38.930 --> 41:41.266
Come here.
What are you doing?

41:44.469 --> 41:47.038
[ Door Opens ]

41:47.172 --> 41:49.875
Hey, baby.

41:57.816 --> 42:01.419
Hey, Vanessa.
Look what we got here.

42:01.587 --> 42:04.890
- Sam, what are you doing?
- Nothing. I'm not doing
anything.

42:05.023 --> 42:09.595
- You're cheatin' on my boy.
- Let's go. Okay?

42:13.198 --> 42:15.834
Come on.

42:26.311 --> 42:29.114
I don't want to get
between you and another guy.

42:29.247 --> 42:31.282
That's just not cool.

42:33.251 --> 42:35.320
I know.

42:37.856 --> 42:41.426
Things are different
with me and Jasper now.

42:41.627 --> 42:44.095
We're not little kids
anymore.

42:46.932 --> 42:49.000
And things change,
right?

42:49.134 --> 42:52.237
Does he know
they've changed?

42:52.370 --> 42:55.974
Let's not talk about this
right now.

42:58.043 --> 43:01.246
I wish we could do
what Frost says.

43:01.379 --> 43:06.652
Leave Earth for a while
and come back and begin
all over.

43:09.855 --> 43:13.992
It would be so nice.
Nice.

43:14.125 --> 43:16.662
Nice.

43:26.037 --> 43:30.709
What you doin'?
Getting away for a while.

43:32.010 --> 43:34.680
- Florida.
- What's Florida?

43:34.813 --> 43:38.316
The southernmost tip
of you.
Mm-hmm.

43:42.187 --> 43:44.189
Mmm.

43:47.726 --> 43:49.728
Florida tickles.

43:49.861 --> 43:54.800
Then let's move north,
shall we?
All right.

43:55.600 --> 43:58.804
Got Georgia peaches.

44:03.474 --> 44:06.712
And South Carolina.

44:06.812 --> 44:10.081
A very beautiful state.

44:11.549 --> 44:15.721
This is North Carolina.

44:18.824 --> 44:22.360
I move further north,

44:22.493 --> 44:24.796
and I find Maryland.

44:30.101 --> 44:32.303
Mmm.

44:32.437 --> 44:36.975
Seems Maryland
tickles too.
I think so.

44:40.278 --> 44:43.749
I suppose that one
there's New York.
Mmm.

44:43.849 --> 44:47.753
That's Jersey.
That's New York.

44:51.322 --> 44:53.992
Planning a visit?

44:54.125 --> 44:56.194
No.

44:56.327 --> 44:59.397
I'm heading towards
Massachusetts.

45:00.365 --> 45:02.868
Massachusetts
welcomes you.

45:36.434 --> 45:38.469
How bad is it?

45:39.504 --> 45:41.807
Is it fixable?

45:44.575 --> 45:46.878
I don't know.
It's pretty bad.

45:51.482 --> 45:53.952
Guess you spoke to Pete.

45:55.921 --> 45:57.823
What are you doing?

45:57.889 --> 46:00.391
I don't know.

46:00.525 --> 46:03.995
This guy walks into town,
and he says a few things,

46:04.129 --> 46:06.832
and he makes you think
a few things.

46:06.965 --> 46:10.869
But it's not real.
We're real.

46:11.002 --> 46:13.271
Me and you.
We've always been real.

46:13.404 --> 46:17.342
I've always known that
we're gonna be together.

46:17.475 --> 46:20.611
I think you have too.

46:20.745 --> 46:23.348
Well, what if
the only reason that--
No. Come on.

46:23.481 --> 46:25.483
Don't do this.

46:27.485 --> 46:30.655
We have a Fourth of July
dance coming up next week.

46:30.856 --> 46:35.160
Clam bake,
camping on the beach.

46:35.293 --> 46:39.397
The whole thing.
Just like last year.
Remember? Come with me.

46:39.530 --> 46:44.402
I mean, this thing with him
is just gonna turn out
to be a thing. You know?

46:44.535 --> 46:48.206
You don't want to waste us
on that, do you?

47:22.407 --> 47:24.910
[ Panting ]

47:26.477 --> 47:28.613
[ Screams ]

47:30.415 --> 47:32.483
[ Panting ]

47:51.402 --> 47:53.571
Ohh, wow.

47:56.174 --> 47:58.977
This is beautiful!

48:00.845 --> 48:03.148
My favorite spot.

48:10.188 --> 48:13.258
So, anyway, there's
this Fourth of July dance.

48:13.391 --> 48:18.196
And, you know, the whole town
goes. It's this tradition.

48:18.329 --> 48:21.832
And they have
fireworks and food...

48:21.967 --> 48:24.369
and people bring
their dates and stuff.

48:24.502 --> 48:29.540
Hey, Samantha.
I would be honored
to be your date.

48:32.710 --> 48:36.547
[ Chuckles ]
Wow. Gosh.

48:36.681 --> 48:41.352
Uh--
Just that I sort of--

48:43.488 --> 48:46.691
[ Sighs ]
I kind of have
to go with Jasper.

48:46.824 --> 48:51.296
[ Chuckles ]
I didn't think things
with you and him were--

48:51.429 --> 48:55.133
I don't know
what they are.
I see.

48:55.266 --> 48:57.835
Do you still have
feelings for him?

48:58.003 --> 49:01.106
Well, of course.
I always will, but...

49:01.239 --> 49:03.908
I'm not--
I mean, it's...

49:04.042 --> 49:07.112
not really--
Um, Samantha,
I don't understand.

49:07.245 --> 49:10.448
I mean, what are you
doing with me?

49:10.581 --> 49:13.218
You've just kind of
taken me by surprise,
you know.

49:13.351 --> 49:15.553
I-- I didn't expect you.

49:15.686 --> 49:19.490
Look, maybe we can get
together after the dance.

49:19.624 --> 49:23.828
I, uh-- I can't because
we're going to Cape Cod.

49:24.029 --> 49:27.165
A-And we--
We go to Cape Cod every year.

49:27.298 --> 49:30.301
Like, don't worry
about it. I mean,

49:30.435 --> 49:34.272
[ Chuckles ]
it's not like we got
some serious thing.

49:34.405 --> 49:38.609
You know, I mean, we're
just havin' fun, right?

49:39.577 --> 49:42.580
[ Softly ]
Right.

49:44.815 --> 49:48.386
[ Phone Rings ]

49:51.322 --> 49:53.591
[ Ringing Continues ]

49:58.163 --> 50:02.733
Hello.
Yes, this is Samantha.

50:03.701 --> 50:06.003
Hi.

50:08.373 --> 50:12.143
Well, did he say
what it was about?

50:15.980 --> 50:18.015
Okay.

50:18.149 --> 50:20.385
Sure,
I'll tell them Tuesday.

50:20.518 --> 50:21.652
Bye.

50:23.754 --> 50:26.624
[ Screen Door Opens ]
[ Jo ]
Who was on the phone?

50:26.757 --> 50:30.395
Somebody selling something.
Oh, don't you
hate that?

50:30.528 --> 50:32.630
Yeah.

50:41.539 --> 50:45.176
Thought you could
call him "Ralph."

50:47.778 --> 50:50.981
I found him
at a pet store
up in Concord.

50:51.116 --> 50:53.017
He's pretty cool,
don't you think?

50:53.151 --> 50:56.554
[ Wheel Squeaking ]
Ralph, Jr.

50:56.687 --> 50:59.490
He's okay, I guess.

50:59.624 --> 51:02.727
I'll let you two
get acquainted.

51:14.939 --> 51:17.242
Hey, Ralph, Jr.

51:19.477 --> 51:22.413
** [ Car Radio Playing Rock ]

51:22.547 --> 51:25.150
[ Engine Turns Off,
Music Stops ]

51:25.250 --> 51:26.951
Hey, Jas, come on!

51:27.152 --> 51:31.289
What's wrong, Richie,
you couldn't find a date?

51:32.157 --> 51:34.825
[ Laughs ]

51:34.959 --> 51:37.495
Jas!
[ Door Opening ]

51:46.171 --> 51:48.406
[ Door Opening ]

51:58.916 --> 51:59.884
Hey.

52:00.017 --> 52:02.287
Hey.
[ Engine Starts ]

52:02.420 --> 52:05.022
[ Woman ]
* I left my couch
And like *

52:05.190 --> 52:09.360
* A crying child *

52:09.494 --> 52:11.829
* Locked the doors behind me *

52:11.962 --> 52:16.301
* Put the pain on file *

52:16.434 --> 52:20.004
* Broken like a window *

52:20.205 --> 52:23.441
* I see my blindness now *

52:23.574 --> 52:26.511
* And I need love *

52:26.644 --> 52:31.282
* Not some sentimental prison *

52:31.416 --> 52:35.052
* I need love *

52:35.220 --> 52:37.755
** [ Continues ]
I can't wait.
Bought this new bathing suit.

52:37.888 --> 52:39.890
It's a one-piece, but
it's mesh in the middle.

52:40.024 --> 52:42.092
Oh, my God.
It's so wicked cool.

52:42.227 --> 52:45.230
I can't explain it.
You got to see it.
It's black, and it's deep dyed.

52:45.363 --> 52:47.732
** [ Continues ]

52:52.237 --> 52:55.005
* Broken like a window *

52:55.139 --> 52:58.876
* I see my blindness now *

52:59.009 --> 53:02.247
* And I need love *

53:02.313 --> 53:06.451
* Not some sentimental prison *

53:06.584 --> 53:10.255
* I need love *

53:10.321 --> 53:12.357
Now, it's for members
of the town, right?

53:12.490 --> 53:15.860
And since I...
am now a proud member...

53:15.993 --> 53:18.896
of this town, then I should
be allowed to go, right?

53:19.029 --> 53:21.666
I should definitely go.
I should absolutely be allowed.

53:21.799 --> 53:25.336
It's settled then.
I am a great dancer.

53:25.470 --> 53:28.072
* I need love *

53:28.273 --> 53:32.477
* Not some sentimental prison *

53:32.610 --> 53:38.949
* I need love **

53:41.286 --> 53:45.556
Who here wants to be my date?
Huh?

53:45.690 --> 53:48.393
Do you... wanna dance?

53:48.526 --> 53:51.562
Come on, baby.
Will you go
to the dance with me?

53:51.696 --> 53:53.898
All right.
Okay. Fine.

53:54.031 --> 53:56.601
[ Cow Mooing ]
Be sure to tip
your waitress.

53:56.734 --> 53:59.604
Adieu.

53:59.737 --> 54:01.339
[ Moos ]

54:01.472 --> 54:04.041
[ Samantha ]
No. No, I hate that hat.
[ Jasper ] You look great.

54:04.174 --> 54:06.344
[ Jasper ]
It's a good hat.

54:06.477 --> 54:08.713
Hey, what's up?

54:10.448 --> 54:13.651
Hey, Kelley.
Hey, Kelley.

54:16.153 --> 54:18.456
Are you drunk?
No.

54:18.589 --> 54:21.859
No.
Why, are you?
No.

54:21.992 --> 54:24.529
Man, maybe you'd
better go, huh?
Go?

54:24.662 --> 54:28.132
Hey, I just got here.
Huh?

54:28.333 --> 54:31.736
Kelley, I think that
you should leave.
Leave? Why?

54:31.869 --> 54:36.774
[ Chuckles ] Oh, farm boy's
getting ready to rumble, huh?
[ Scoffs ]

54:36.907 --> 54:39.844
Come on.
Come on, dance with me.

54:39.977 --> 54:42.747
Huh? Jasper doesn't mind,
do you, Jasper?

54:42.880 --> 54:45.783
I think you better go,
before I kick-- All right?
Hey. Hey.

54:45.916 --> 54:48.853
Hey, what's everybody
getting so huffy for, huh?

54:48.986 --> 54:50.755
Huh? Relax.

54:50.888 --> 54:53.057
Hey,
gonna dance with you.
[ Muttering ]

54:53.190 --> 54:54.892
[ Grunts ]

54:56.160 --> 54:58.363
Come on.

54:58.496 --> 55:00.898
[ Groans ]

56:35.926 --> 56:40.030
Where you going?
Back to Boston.

56:40.164 --> 56:41.832
What about
your probation?

56:41.966 --> 56:43.834
You could've
just danced with me.

56:43.968 --> 56:47.371
- I was there with a date.
- I should've been your date!

56:47.505 --> 56:49.474
I thought that
I explained that to you.

56:49.607 --> 56:52.910
Yeah,
you made your choice.

56:54.144 --> 56:56.180
Kelley, that's not fair.

56:58.248 --> 57:00.551
Look, come with me.
What?

57:00.685 --> 57:03.788
Come to Boston.
I can't go
with you to Boston.

57:03.921 --> 57:06.857
Just for the weekend.
You can be back by Sunday.

57:08.693 --> 57:11.962
Look, Samantha.
We don't have to hide.

57:12.096 --> 57:14.565
We can be together.

57:34.552 --> 57:36.921
[ Door Hisses ]

57:50.300 --> 57:52.703
What's goin' on?

57:54.071 --> 57:55.740
Sam?

57:55.873 --> 57:58.943
What did you say to him?

58:00.645 --> 58:04.649
I can't go...

58:04.782 --> 58:07.084
with you, Jasper.

58:09.019 --> 58:11.689
What?

58:16.460 --> 58:20.397
I can't be with you.
What? No--
Stop sayin' that.

58:20.565 --> 58:23.901
Just--
Just come with me, okay?

58:24.034 --> 58:27.204
Me and you were
supposed to be together.

58:27.337 --> 58:29.306
I just don't know anymore.

58:29.439 --> 58:33.443
[ Chuckles ]
N-Nobody knows you
like I do, all right?

58:33.578 --> 58:36.781
Nobody--
Nobody sees you like I do.

58:38.448 --> 58:41.018
We belong together.

58:41.151 --> 58:43.287
We--

58:44.188 --> 58:48.458
I love you.
I-I-I love you, Sam.

58:48.593 --> 58:50.861
I have to go.

58:52.763 --> 58:55.800
[ Whispers ]
I'm sorry.

59:12.049 --> 59:17.888
[ Man ]
* Figure of divine perfection *

59:18.022 --> 59:23.861
* No one's loved
with more affection *

59:23.994 --> 59:28.899
* Soul to soul we breathe *

59:29.033 --> 59:35.039
* Oh, I won't let
the fates succeed *

59:36.240 --> 59:41.879
* Worried hours
of contemplation *

59:42.012 --> 59:47.117
* Whispered bits
of conversation *

59:48.185 --> 59:53.323
* Unaffected orderlies *

59:53.457 --> 59:58.428
* Disinfected
rooms and hallways *

59:58.562 --> 01:00:04.368
* And if you sleep
you sleep with God *

01:00:04.501 --> 01:00:09.974
* And if I cry
it's for my heart *

01:00:10.107 --> 01:00:12.643
* 'Cause if you sleep *

01:00:12.777 --> 01:00:17.214
* I'll sleep too **

01:00:17.347 --> 01:00:19.750
Where's your butler?

01:00:19.884 --> 01:00:23.187
[ Chuckles ]
Well,

01:00:23.320 --> 01:00:27.758
it's Fourth of July weekend
plus my dad's out of town, so--

01:00:29.626 --> 01:00:32.229
Can you show me
around your mansion?
[ Scoffs ]

01:00:32.997 --> 01:00:35.065
It's just a house.

01:00:35.199 --> 01:00:38.035
Come on, let's go see
if there's food
in the kitchen.

01:00:42.172 --> 01:00:44.241
How 'bout...

01:00:45.442 --> 01:00:47.511
I take the tour...

01:00:47.644 --> 01:00:49.880
myself!

01:00:57.855 --> 01:01:00.590
Marco.

01:01:00.725 --> 01:01:03.994
Polo.

01:01:11.201 --> 01:01:13.270
Marco.

01:01:13.403 --> 01:01:15.740
Polo.

01:01:25.950 --> 01:01:28.252
Hey, Samantha?

01:01:31.321 --> 01:01:33.858
Samantha, come on.

01:01:33.991 --> 01:01:36.426
Game's over.

01:01:42.499 --> 01:01:45.770
- Samantha, get out of the tub.
- What's the matter?

01:01:45.903 --> 01:01:48.906
Just get out of the tub.

01:01:49.039 --> 01:01:51.909
Kelley, what's wrong?

01:01:53.443 --> 01:01:55.846
Kelley--

01:02:20.938 --> 01:02:23.507
You okay?

01:02:31.849 --> 01:02:34.118
My mother loved her roses.

01:02:36.220 --> 01:02:41.191
She would just sit in here
for hours and stare at 'em,
breathin' 'em in.

01:02:44.494 --> 01:02:48.665
They only bloom once a year
at the end of summer, but...

01:02:48.833 --> 01:02:52.837
she always said that's
what made 'em so special.

01:02:52.903 --> 01:02:57.274
And then just fade away.

01:03:08.052 --> 01:03:10.454
In the summers
when I was a kid,

01:03:10.587 --> 01:03:13.723
she used to take me outside
to stand in the rain.

01:03:13.858 --> 01:03:16.894
She said it was good
for our hair.

01:03:17.995 --> 01:03:20.865
Hers was so long.

01:03:21.966 --> 01:03:24.869
So beautiful.

01:03:33.878 --> 01:03:35.579
I found her in the tub.

01:03:35.712 --> 01:03:41.118
The water was
so thick with blood,
it looked like paint.

01:03:41.251 --> 01:03:46.423
I tried to wrap
a towel around her wrist
to stop the bleeding.

01:03:46.556 --> 01:03:49.894
But she wasn't bleeding.

01:03:50.760 --> 01:03:53.530
It was
all in the tub.

01:03:55.032 --> 01:03:57.902
I always knew
my mother was sad,
you know?

01:04:03.040 --> 01:04:05.509
She didn't say a word.

01:04:07.945 --> 01:04:10.347
She just gave up.

01:06:13.670 --> 01:06:16.473
I wonder what
the world record is
for staying in bed.

01:06:16.606 --> 01:06:20.044
[ Chuckles ]
I bet we could
break it easy.

01:06:23.413 --> 01:06:25.549
Stay here?

01:06:25.682 --> 01:06:29.319
I'm gonna
make you breakfast.

01:06:30.920 --> 01:06:34.858
[ Chuckles ]
What about the record?

01:06:35.059 --> 01:06:38.728
[ Woman ]
* Whatever turns you on
turns me on *

01:06:38.862 --> 01:06:42.799
* Oh, let's get started
Ohh, that's right *

01:06:42.932 --> 01:06:45.935
* Whatever turns you on
turns me on *

01:06:46.070 --> 01:06:48.205
* Oh, baby, I'm there *

01:06:48.338 --> 01:06:50.640
* I ain't scared *

01:06:50.774 --> 01:06:54.678
* We're spinnin'
round and round
and upside down *

01:06:54.811 --> 01:06:58.548
* Flyin' left and right
Don't crash this flight *

01:06:58.682 --> 01:07:03.153
* From north and south
I'm all I found *

01:07:03.287 --> 01:07:07.524
** [ Continues ]

01:07:07.657 --> 01:07:10.294
* Whatever turns you on
turns me on *

01:07:10.427 --> 01:07:12.396
* Oh, let's get started **
[ Footsteps ]

01:07:12.529 --> 01:07:14.698
I thought I told you
to wait in bed?

01:07:14.831 --> 01:07:18.802
I have a feeling it might
get a little crowded.

01:07:24.341 --> 01:07:26.610
I'll get Kelley.

01:07:27.777 --> 01:07:30.647
[ Faucet Squeaks ]

01:07:34.551 --> 01:07:37.421
So, how did you
and Kelley meet?

01:07:37.554 --> 01:07:41.758
He burned down
my family's restaurant.
Oh.

01:07:43.660 --> 01:07:46.330
I don't believe you'd bring
a woman into Mom's house.

01:07:46.463 --> 01:07:49.133
Don't you even think about
turning this around on me.

01:07:49.233 --> 01:07:52.936
First of all,
this is my house, and this
is a discussion about you...

01:07:53.137 --> 01:07:55.739
and the fact that
you continue to be
so reckless with your life.

01:07:55.872 --> 01:08:00.444
- Dad, it's my life.
- No! Everything that
you do reflects on me.

01:08:02.712 --> 01:08:05.582
What you're gonna do now is
you're going back to Putnam
immediately.

01:08:05.715 --> 01:08:07.651
You will complete
your obligation there.

01:08:07.784 --> 01:08:10.687
- And in three week's time,
you will start at Princeton.
- Dad, why?

01:08:10.820 --> 01:08:14.158
Why do I have to start early?
Why can't I just start
with everybody else?

01:08:14.291 --> 01:08:17.861
I had to pull a lot
of strings to make
this happen, and you're going.

01:08:17.993 --> 01:08:20.596
is a very nice distraction.

01:08:20.729 --> 01:08:22.799
That's what it is.
Just a distraction.

01:08:22.932 --> 01:08:25.202
It's not your life.

01:08:26.336 --> 01:08:29.072
You have much bigger
things ahead of you.

01:08:29.206 --> 01:08:32.809
Now get your eyes
forward, already.

01:08:35.078 --> 01:08:37.413
I think you have
a bus to catch.

01:09:05.675 --> 01:09:10.113
[ Door Squeaking ]
[ Sighs ] So what is it
you think you're doing?

01:09:10.247 --> 01:09:13.750
What is it that
you think I'm doing?
I don't know.

01:09:13.883 --> 01:09:16.286
But whatever it is,
it is gonna stop!
[ Phone Ringing ]

01:09:16.420 --> 01:09:18.221
What's
gonna stop?
You know what he is!

01:09:18.287 --> 01:09:20.357
No. And you have
no idea what he is!
Will you
get the phone?

01:09:20.490 --> 01:09:22.792
Didn't you learn
from your sister?
I'm not Jen.

01:09:22.926 --> 01:09:25.529
I'm walking into this
with my eyes open.
What
is it you're walking into?

01:09:25.662 --> 01:09:27.831
A relationship...
with this kid?

01:09:27.964 --> 01:09:30.466
He's gonna be gone
in a few weeks. You're not
gonna hear from him again.

01:09:30.600 --> 01:09:32.868
Well, maybe
he's different.
Tell me how.

01:09:33.002 --> 01:09:35.671
Maybe he loves me.
He doesn't know
the meaning of the word!

01:09:35.805 --> 01:09:39.443
And you don't know him.
[ Jo ] That was
Dr. Falco's office.

01:09:39.576 --> 01:09:44.348
- What did he want?
- He wanted to confirm your
appointment for tomorrow.

01:09:44.481 --> 01:09:49.618
They said they talked to you.
Why didn't you tell us?
'Cause I'm not going.

01:09:49.752 --> 01:09:53.390
Why?
Because I'm fine.
And my knee is fine.

01:09:53.523 --> 01:09:56.826
And it's been fine.
And I'm sick
of talking about it!

01:10:02.399 --> 01:10:04.668
Samantha!

01:10:12.609 --> 01:10:15.211
I'm looking
for Samantha.

01:10:15.345 --> 01:10:17.647
I haven't seen her.

01:10:18.815 --> 01:10:21.985
[ Sighs ]
Well, if you see her,

01:10:22.118 --> 01:10:25.989
just tell her it's
important she come home.

01:10:26.122 --> 01:10:28.758
Look, I'm asking,
Kelley.

01:10:28.892 --> 01:10:30.760
Okay?

01:10:58.087 --> 01:11:00.256
Is everything okay?

01:11:00.390 --> 01:11:02.859
Yeah.

01:11:05.395 --> 01:11:08.532
I love this spot.

01:11:10.800 --> 01:11:15.171
It's like heaven...
right here on earth.

01:11:15.339 --> 01:11:17.974
Maybe that's
what heaven is.

01:11:18.107 --> 01:11:22.746
Maybe we go through life
collecting people
and places we love.

01:11:24.548 --> 01:11:26.650
And they
become our heaven.

01:11:26.783 --> 01:11:29.386
And that's where
your mom is.

01:11:29.519 --> 01:11:34.724
She's in her heaven surrounded
by everything that she loves.

01:11:37.494 --> 01:11:39.363
Including you.

01:11:39.429 --> 01:11:43.567
You think so?
Yeah.

01:11:52.376 --> 01:11:54.644
Let's race.

01:11:56.946 --> 01:11:59.549
Sam--

01:12:04.388 --> 01:12:07.791
[ Panting ]

01:12:31.180 --> 01:12:33.483
[ Groans ]

01:12:33.617 --> 01:12:36.085
Samantha!
[ Sobbing ]

01:12:36.219 --> 01:12:39.055
What happened?
Are you okay?

01:12:39.188 --> 01:12:42.058
[ Moaning, Weeping ]

01:12:42.191 --> 01:12:44.928
So, what's the matter?

01:12:45.962 --> 01:12:49.499
Samantha,
what is it?
[ Sobbing ]

01:12:49.633 --> 01:12:52.836
There's something
I have to tell you.

01:13:07.651 --> 01:13:11.588
Boy, how does it go
from her leg to her liver?

01:13:11.721 --> 01:13:13.890
That's how
osteosarcoma works.

01:13:14.023 --> 01:13:16.460
We always knew that
this was a possibility.

01:13:16.560 --> 01:13:18.462
What can we do?
[ Sighs ]

01:13:18.528 --> 01:13:21.465
I wish there was a list
of options I could give you,
but there just isn't.

01:13:21.531 --> 01:13:23.967
[ Sighs ]
It just
moved so fast.

01:13:39.483 --> 01:13:40.750
Sam.

01:13:42.852 --> 01:13:44.488
Hey.

01:13:44.588 --> 01:13:48.024
I'm gonna go for a walk.
I'll be back in a minute.

01:13:56.132 --> 01:13:58.167
Come and sit with me.

01:14:18.588 --> 01:14:21.525
Kelley--

01:14:22.526 --> 01:14:25.529
When you tell someone
you have cancer,

01:14:27.230 --> 01:14:30.900
no matter how you say it,
they just end up
feeling sorry for you.

01:14:32.135 --> 01:14:36.005
And I didn't want you
feeling sorry for me.

01:14:37.907 --> 01:14:40.544
Could you die from this?

01:14:42.411 --> 01:14:45.181
I am gonna die
from this.

01:14:45.314 --> 01:14:49.919
There's-- There's nothing
that they can do for you?
Sure,

01:14:50.053 --> 01:14:51.855
there are things
they can do.

01:14:51.988 --> 01:14:54.891
They're just not
the right things for me.

01:14:55.024 --> 01:14:58.161
But if they can save you--
Won't.

01:14:58.294 --> 01:15:00.864
It's already spread.

01:15:00.997 --> 01:15:03.266
Even with the treatment,
the best they can offer...

01:15:03.399 --> 01:15:06.803
is a chance I could
live a year or two.

01:15:08.605 --> 01:15:10.840
It's not worth it.

01:15:14.410 --> 01:15:18.147
So, what?
You just gonna give up?

01:15:22.619 --> 01:15:24.487
You just gonna die?

01:15:24.621 --> 01:15:28.291
No.

01:15:28.424 --> 01:15:32.596
I'm going to live.

01:15:33.496 --> 01:15:37.133
Just not as long as you.

01:15:56.185 --> 01:15:58.221
[ Horn Honking ]

01:16:00.624 --> 01:16:03.627
Come look at this stuff.

01:16:03.693 --> 01:16:07.631
** [ Woman Singing ]
Found it at an old place
out on Ridge Road.

01:16:07.764 --> 01:16:10.199
Oh, yeah.

01:16:10.333 --> 01:16:12.435
Jasper, Kelley,
come here.

01:16:12.636 --> 01:16:17.907
* There were angels *
This, uh, English pine--
nice and soft.

01:16:18.041 --> 01:16:20.409
Good for carving.
Look at that.

01:16:20.543 --> 01:16:24.447
* We won't lose track *

01:16:24.648 --> 01:16:29.085
* 'Cause a part of our backs *

01:16:29.218 --> 01:16:34.023
* Feel the weight of wings *

01:16:37.761 --> 01:16:41.130
* Why they fall
it's hard to tell *

01:16:41.264 --> 01:16:43.800
* But some things you can't *

01:16:43.933 --> 01:16:47.971
* Buy or sell *

01:16:49.505 --> 01:16:53.810
* Yeah, we only hurt
the ones we love *

01:16:53.943 --> 01:16:57.881
* While we don't
need a reason *

01:16:58.014 --> 01:17:01.718
* Only give up the thing
we deserve *

01:17:01.851 --> 01:17:03.687
* And that's something *

01:17:03.787 --> 01:17:08.725
* To believe in **

01:17:08.858 --> 01:17:13.697
[ Knocking ]
Samantha? There's
a young man here to see you.

01:17:19.235 --> 01:17:21.070
Hey.

01:17:33.449 --> 01:17:37.754
So you're comin' home
in a couple of days?
Yeah.

01:17:38.587 --> 01:17:41.457
It's good, right?

01:17:41.590 --> 01:17:43.860
It's great.

01:17:49.733 --> 01:17:52.736
Jas?

01:17:52.802 --> 01:17:54.938
About that night?

01:17:55.071 --> 01:17:57.406
Oh.

01:17:57.540 --> 01:18:00.443
We don't have
to talk about it.

01:18:02.078 --> 01:18:04.480
Just wanted to say
that I'm sorry.

01:18:04.748 --> 01:18:08.852
Well... I'm sorry.

01:18:08.985 --> 01:18:11.988
What do you have
to be sorry for?

01:18:12.121 --> 01:18:15.058
I haven't been
a very good friend.

01:18:17.560 --> 01:18:21.564
You've been
my best friend.

01:18:21.765 --> 01:18:24.433
You'll always be
my best friend.

01:18:24.567 --> 01:18:26.870
Always.

01:18:32.776 --> 01:18:35.779
I really do love you.

01:18:36.980 --> 01:18:40.283
I love you too.

01:18:41.617 --> 01:18:44.253
[ Sniffling ]

01:18:59.368 --> 01:19:01.938
[ Chattering ]

01:19:09.112 --> 01:19:12.949
That's in there.
Got it?

01:19:13.082 --> 01:19:15.819
Bring it--
Bring it right there.

01:19:17.720 --> 01:19:21.925
[ Electric Drill
Whirring ]

01:20:07.904 --> 01:20:09.538
How's she doin'?

01:20:09.672 --> 01:20:13.442
If you care so much,
why don't you go down
and see her?

01:20:13.576 --> 01:20:16.079
What's it to you?

01:20:17.180 --> 01:20:19.883
Because
I do care about her.

01:20:20.016 --> 01:20:24.020
For whatever reason,
she needs you.

01:20:24.153 --> 01:20:27.023
Am I supposed to stay?

01:20:28.291 --> 01:20:30.393
I'm not from Putnam,
remember?

01:20:32.461 --> 01:20:34.330
I've got a life
to get back to.

01:20:36.732 --> 01:20:41.370
Do you know how much
it kills me every time that
I see her look at you?

01:20:42.872 --> 01:20:46.775
Every time I hear her say
your name, for Chrisakes?

01:20:46.910 --> 01:20:51.214
But no matter how much
it tears me up inside
to see you with her,

01:20:51.347 --> 01:20:53.716
the one thing that
I want right now...

01:20:53.849 --> 01:20:55.718
is for you
to get over your shit...

01:20:55.851 --> 01:20:58.121
